Beat the sugar and butter together.Add the eggs and fold in the flour.Add the orange and lemon zest.Grease a small, heat-resistant glass pudding bowl, then drizzle the honey inside the bowl.Pour the pudding mixture into the bowl.Cover the bowl with cling film and microwave the bowl on high for 4-5 minutes, or until the sponge is cooked.Remove sponge from microwave and discard the cling film.Tip the sponge out onto a flat plate.Top sponge with combined whipped cream and apple sauce and the nuts and serve while still hot.